column18: 05/16/2016: Assailants attacked a police station in Les Cayes, Sud, Haiti. At least seven people, including a police officer and six assailants were killed in the attack. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
column108: The extent of damage to the police station is unknown, however; weapons were stolen in this attack.
column125: Casualty numbers for this attack conflict across sources. Following GTD protocol, the most recent reliable estimates are reported here.
